79. Create a PHP program to append two files in another file.
ANSWER
Steps:
1.Read contents of file1.txt and file2.txt.
2.Append both to merged.txt.
3.Use file_get_contents() and file_put_contents() with FILE_APPEND.

<?php
// Set filenames
$file1 = 'file1.txt';
$file2 = 'file2.txt';
$outputFile = 'combined.txt';
// Check if both input files exist
if (!file_exists($file1) || !file_exists($file2)) {
    echo "One or both input files do not exist.";
    exit;
}
// Read contents from file1 and file2
$content1 = file_get_contents($file1);
$content2 = file_get_contents($file2);
// Combine the contents with line breaks
$combinedContent = $content1 . PHP_EOL . $content2 . PHP_EOL;
// Append to output file (creates it if it doesn't exist)
if (file_put_contents($outputFile, $combinedContent, FILE_APPEND | LOCK_EX) !== false) {
    echo "✅ Files successfully appended to '$outputFile'.";
} else {
    echo "❌ Failed to write to '$outputFile'.";
}
?>

OUTPUT
One or both input files do not exist.

